We had been waiting there for an hour outside, it was the Cape Coral Art and Music Festival 2020 (so you would think they would have been ready for this kind of traffic) and everything went wrong. They didn't have any salad, they don't have any other bun choices besides one, they didn't have a fair amount of toppings...what in the world? The owner wrote me to explain that the have a limited menu during events? Well I'm unsure how I was suppose to know this when we weren't told? And why would you take off a gluten free bun? Excluding people with food allergies during an event doesn't seem like a smart business move.  The wait staff were doing the best they can and were kind but when we waited over roughly an hour to be told "sorry we don't have the gluten free bun you ordered an hour ago...here's a regular bun!" I couldnt help but be irritated. As someone who has worked in a consistently busy burger place and worked on the grill, burgers just are not that hard to make...especially with a limited menu.

I have a new favorite burger place in the Cape. And these don't come with your run of the mill lettuce/tomato/pickle toppings either; although you can order it that way since they let you design your own.  My wife and I met here for lunch today - Friday at 11:30. There was ample seating, but the tables filled up as the lunch rush filed in. The restaurant is brightly colored, and plays oldies music in the background. There are also umbrella covered tables outside with music playing there too.  Our waitress arrived quickly and took our drink orders and asked if we'd been there before (we hadn't). She explained the lunch specials as well as how to build our own creation with their ample list of toppings. As I said, this isn't your typical list. Lehne Burger has the normal stuff of course; but why stop there when you can add fried egg, hashbrowns, or French fried onions to your burger. Or if you have a sweet tooth, maybe marshmallows, grilled banana, and peanut butter? The list goes on to include things like grilled pineapple, cheese curds, coleslaw, ghost pepper cheese, roasted cashews, etc. The extras will cost you though, so keep that in mind as you're designing your creation. Their list of sauces is just as impressive with dressings like Chipotle mayo, parmesan garlic, and Mike's hot honey sauce.  I chose one of the specials and for $9.99 got the Lehne BBQ Burger with fries and a drink. Within two bites, I knew I'd be coming back here again. My Angus burger was done perfectly (medium) and came with the usual toppings along with smoked bacon, fresh red onion, a slab of hashbrowns, and BBQ sauce. The bun was fresh (I'm getting the pretzel bun next time) and they have gluten free buns available. This was by far the best tasting burger I've had in years. My wife (who's  burger was topped with a fried egg and served over a salad instead of a bun) agreed. We will be returning here soon. I have to save room for dessert though next time; that Nutella milkshake was calling my name.

I absolutely loved the burger.  Wasn't thrilled with the fries, found them salty and soggy. For $9.99 you get a large sized burger with toppings of your choice.  Wish you could buy just the burger as I know I or a family member could probably eat two at a meal.
